# CODEOWNERS for shekyl-core
#
# Path-based mandatory review. GitHub uses the LAST matching pattern,
# so order specific paths AFTER general ones.
#
# Authority for this file: docs/V3_WALLET_DECISION_LOG.md
# (decision: "KAT regression CI: plain tests, dedicated files,
# CODEOWNERS + branch protection", 2026-04-25).
#
# Branch protection on `dev` requires PR review; PR review for paths
# below requires the listed maintainers as approvers, regardless of
# any other approving reviews.

# -----------------------------------------------------------------
# Test-vector corpus (KAT regression).
#
# Any change to a published test vector is a freeze-relevant action.
# Two-maintainer review per the freeze plan.
# -----------------------------------------------------------------
docs/test_vectors/**                   @Shekyl-Foundation/maintainers
docs/test_vectors/WALLET_FILE_FORMAT_V1/**  @Shekyl-Foundation/maintainers
/tests/kat_*.rs                        @Shekyl-Foundation/maintainers
/rust/**/tests/kat_*.rs                @Shekyl-Foundation/maintainers

# -----------------------------------------------------------------
# Freeze-relevant specs and design documents.
#
# Touching these implies a wire-format or algorithm-stability
# decision that needs maintainer review.
# -----------------------------------------------------------------
docs/POST_QUANTUM_CRYPTOGRAPHY.md      @Shekyl-Foundation/maintainers
docs/FCMP_PLUS_PLUS.md                 @Shekyl-Foundation/maintainers
docs/WALLET_FILE_FORMAT.md             @Shekyl-Foundation/maintainers
docs/SIGNING.md                        @Shekyl-Foundation/maintainers

# -----------------------------------------------------------------
# Decision log (append-only).
#
# Entries here are binding for new code. Maintainer review on every
# addition keeps the log from drifting into per-author opinions.
# -----------------------------------------------------------------
docs/V3_WALLET_DECISION_LOG.md         @Shekyl-Foundation/maintainers

# -----------------------------------------------------------------
# Release-machinery and CI policy files.
